// Dead-man's-switch: fires when any machine's last heartbeat is older than the
// 72h tolerance, OR when the whole telemetry pipeline goes silent.
//
// Data source is the hub watchdog cron (*/15), NOT raw heartbeats. The watchdog
// (hub/src/cron/watchdog.ts) iterates the D1 `machines` roster and emits, for
// EVERY machine — including long-silent ones — a structured log:
//   { event: "hub.machine.heartbeat_age", machine: <id>, age_seconds: <n> }
// Workers observability ships this as an OTLP log whose Body is that JSON string;
// this project's DCR (infra/azure/provision.sh) lands OTLP logs in the Log
// Analytics **OTelLogs** table (confirmed live 2026-07-17: a synthetic OTLP log
// through the gateway landed in OTelLogs with the JSON in the `Body` column).
//
// Why a gauge and not an absence JOIN over hub.heartbeat: Azure scheduled-query
// rules cap overrideQueryTimeRange at 2880 min (48h), shorter than the 72h
// tolerance, so a machine silent >48h would drop out of any self-referential
// baseline and the alert would self-silence. The watchdog re-emits a fresh,
// growing age for a dead machine every 15 min, so a short scan window always has
// current data and the alert never self-silences. No overrideQueryTimeRange is
// needed (provision.sh's default window covers it).
//
// Pipeline-dead detection (the other half of "dead-man"): if the gateway, the
// observability export destination, or the watchdog cron itself stops delivering
// logs, the liveness window has NO watchdog output at all — a bare stale-machine
// query would then return zero rows and provision.sh's `count > 0` rule would
// read that outage as HEALTHY. So we union in a synthetic `__pipeline_silent__`
// row whenever the window contains no `hub.watchdog.run` beacon.
//
// Liveness-leg lookback = 1h, matching the rule's hourly evaluation cadence
// (provision.sh: evaluation-frequency == window-size == 1h for missed-heartbeat).
// A shorter lookback than the cadence leaves an unobserved gap each hour — a
// total-pipeline outage that starts and recovers inside that gap would never be
// seen. Tiling the 1h lookback to the 1h cadence closes it. Only the two liveness
// legs (pipeline_silent, roster_unavailable) need this; stale_machines keeps its
// 30m arg_max window because it keys on the re-emitted age_seconds gauge, not on
// the presence/absence of rows.
//
// Crucially the silence check keys on the `hub.watchdog.run` BEACON, not on the
// count of heartbeat_age rows: the watchdog emits the beacon every run even with
// an empty machine roster, so a fresh deploy before any machine enrols (a
// legitimate live state) stays quiet instead of false-paging. The beacon is
// absent only when the cron/gateway/export path is genuinely dead.
//
// Roster-read failure (third leg): the watchdog stamps `roster_ok:false` on its
// beacon when the D1 roster read throws — the beacon still goes out (pipeline is
// alive) but NO heartbeat_age rows are emitted that run, so stale-machine
// detection is blind. We fire `__roster_unavailable__` when ANY beacon in the
// window has roster_ok == false — not just the latest: a transient roster failure
// that recovers before evaluation still left stale-machine monitoring blind for
// that stretch, and arg_max on the latest beacon alone would erase it.
//
// The email's machine value says which case fired: a real machine_id (stale
// collector), __pipeline_silent__ (telemetry pipeline down), or
// __roster_unavailable__ (hub alive but can't read its machine table). NOTE: the
// pipeline_silent row does fire until the account-level observability
// destinations are wired and sessions-hub is redeployed to export (see
// infra/cf/telemetry.md) — correct, telemetry genuinely isn't flowing until then.
//
// Missing-table guard (`otel`): the OTelLogs table doesn't exist until the FIRST
// OTLP log lands. A bare `OTelLogs` reference then fails to RESOLVE at evaluation
// time (a SemanticError, distinct from returning zero rows) — and a rule whose
// query errors never fires, so the pipeline_silent dead-man would be blind during
// exactly the bootstrap / total-export-outage window it exists for
// (skip-query-validation only lets the rule be created, not evaluated). Wrapping
// the table in `union isfuzzy=true (empty datatable), (OTelLogs | ...)` degrades
// a missing table to the empty datatable instead of erroring, so every leg still
// evaluates and pipeline_silent still synthesizes its row. Verified live: the
// isfuzzy union returns identical results against the real table and returns the
// datatable side (no error) when the unioned table name doesn't exist.

let otel = union isfuzzy=true
    (datatable(TimeGenerated:datetime, Body:string)[]),
    (OTelLogs | project TimeGenerated, Body);
let stale_machines = otel
    | where TimeGenerated > ago(30m)
    | extend body = todynamic(Body)
    | where body.event == "hub.machine.heartbeat_age"
    | extend machine = tostring(body.machine), age_seconds = tolong(body.age_seconds)
    | summarize arg_max(TimeGenerated, age_seconds) by machine
    | where age_seconds > 72 * 3600
    | project machine, age_seconds;
let pipeline_silent = otel
    | where TimeGenerated > ago(1h)
    | extend body = todynamic(Body)
    | where body.event == "hub.watchdog.run"
    | summarize n = count()
    | where n == 0
    | project machine = "__pipeline_silent__", age_seconds = tolong(-1);
let roster_unavailable = otel
    | where TimeGenerated > ago(1h)
    | extend body = todynamic(Body)
    | where body.event == "hub.watchdog.run"
    | extend roster_ok = tobool(body.roster_ok)
    | where roster_ok == false
    | summarize n = count()
    | where n > 0
    | project machine = "__roster_unavailable__", age_seconds = tolong(-1);
// pipeline_silent only catches a FULLY empty window. A mid-window outage that
// recovers before evaluation (beacon 09:15, silence to 09:55, eval 10:00) leaves
// beacons in the 1h window, so silence-by-emptiness misses it. pipeline_gap does
// gap analysis instead: take the run beacons, inject the window's own edges
// (window start and now()) so a hole at either end counts, order them, and take
// the largest consecutive gap. Fire __pipeline_gap__ (age_seconds = gap length in
// seconds) when that gap exceeds 35m — two missed 15-min beacons — so one delayed
// tick stays quiet. Guarded to real beacons present (edges - 2 > 0); the fully
// empty window is left to pipeline_silent, the clearer "nothing at all" signal.
let pipeline_gap = union
        (otel
            | where TimeGenerated > ago(1h)
            | extend body = todynamic(Body)
            | where body.event == "hub.watchdog.run"
            | project TimeGenerated),
        (print TimeGenerated = ago(1h)),
        (print TimeGenerated = now())
    | order by TimeGenerated asc
    | serialize gap = TimeGenerated - prev(TimeGenerated)
    | summarize max_gap = max(gap), edges_plus_real = count()
    | where (edges_plus_real - 2) > 0 and max_gap > 35m
    | project machine = "__pipeline_gap__", age_seconds = tolong(max_gap / 1s);
stale_machines
| union pipeline_silent, roster_unavailable, pipeline_gap
